Package com.team1389.hardware.inputs.hardware

  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    ADXRS453_Gyro
    Use a rate gyro to return the robots heading relative to a starting position.
    DashboardBinaryInput
    tracks a boolean on the network table and makes its value available as a stream
    DashboardInput<T>
    tracks a piece of data on the network table and makes its value available as a stream
    DashboardScalarInput
    tracks a double on the network table and makes its value available as a stream
    GyroHardware
    wraps a WPILib AnalogGyro, providing stream sources for the gyro position and rate
    JoystickHardware
    offers stream sources for all values available from the WPILib joystick
    NavXHardware
    wraps a Kauailabs NavX, providing stream sources for the yaw, rate, etc.
    PDPHardware
    represents a Power Distribution Panel attached to the robot's CAN interface can track the current being drawn from ports on the PDP
    PotentiometerHardware
    represents an analog potentiometer
    SwitchHardware
    represents any digital input (hall effect, infared proximity, limit switches, etc)
    TimedBoolean
    a boolean stream that becomes true after a fixed wait time
    Timer
    wraps the WPILib timer class
